  "name": "Compound Engineering",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "AI-powered development toolkit with specialized agents, commands, and skills for planning, reviewing, researching, and compounding engineering knowledge.",
  "longDescription": "Marketplace plugin containing 2 sub-plugins. The main `compound-engineering` plugin ships 29 agents (15 reviewers including Rails, TypeScript, Python, security, performance, and data integrity specialists; 5 research agents; 3 design agents; 5 workflow agents), 22 commands (including `/workflows:plan`, `/workflows:work`, `/workflows:review`, `/workflows:compound`), 19 skills (browser automation, git worktree management, image generation, swarm orchestration, and more), and 1 MCP server (`context7`). Also includes a `coding-tutor` sub-plugin with 3 commands and 1 skill for spaced-repetition coding tutorials. Includes a CLI (`bunx @every-env/compound-plugin`) for syncing to OpenCode, Codex, Cursor, Droid, and Pi.",
